Chesapeake sees Q4 net $ 7 . 4 mln , $ 0 . 23 / shr . Chesapeake Energy Corp said on Thursday it expected to report net earnings of $ 7 . 4 million , or $ 0 . 23 per share , on total revenue of $ 49 . 5 million in the fourth quarter ended June 30 . This compares with net earnings of $ 3 . 8 million , or $ 0 . 13 per common share , on total revenue of $ 23 . 4 million in the same quarter last year . For the year , it said it expected to report earnings of $ 23 . 4 million , or $ 0 . 80 per share , on total revenue of $ 149 . 4 million , for the fiscal 1996 year ended June 30 . Chesapeake expects to release final results for the fourth quarter and year - end periods on or before September 15 . It said that as of June 30 , its estimated future net revenue attributable to its proved reserves , before income taxes and discounted at 10 percent , was $ 547 million , a 193 percent increase over last year ' s present value of $ 187 million . Of the company ' s proved reserves , 45 percent are located in Oklahoma , 41 percent in Texas and 14 percent in Louisiana and other , it said . 
